  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Get answers to the most commonly asked questions about credit cards</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What is the minimum CIBIL score required to get a credit card?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Most banks require a minimum CIBIL score of 700 to approve a regular credit card application. However, if your score is between 600-700, you may still qualify for certain entry-level or secured credit cards. Secured credit cards, which are backed by a fixed deposit, can be obtained with scores as low as 300. A higher credit score (750+) improves your chances of getting premium cards with better rewards and higher credit limits.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What is the difference between a credit card and a debit card?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              A debit card deducts money directly from your bank account when you make a purchase, while a credit card lets you borrow money from the bank up to a pre-approved limit. With a credit card, you get a billing cycle (typically 20-50 days) to repay without interest. Credit cards also offer rewards, cashback, and purchase protection that debit cards typically don't. Using a credit card responsibly helps build your credit score, which is beneficial for future loan applications.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How can I avoid paying credit card annual fees?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              There are several ways to avoid annual fees: (1) Apply for lifetime free credit cards like ICICI Amazon Pay or Axis ACE that have zero joining and annual fees. (2) Many cards waive the annual fee if you meet a minimum annual spending threshold — for example, spending ₹1 lakh or more per year. (3) Call your bank's customer service and request a fee waiver; banks often agree to retain loyal customers. (4) Look for limited-period offers where banks waive fees for the first year or more.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How long does it take to get a credit card after applying?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              The processing time depends on the bank and the type of card. For instant or pre-approved credit cards, you can get a digital card within minutes and start using it for online purchases immediately. The physical card typically arrives within 7-10 business days via courier. For regular applications, banks take 3-5 business days to verify your documents and approve the application. Once approved, the physical card is dispatched and reaches you within 7-14 working days.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What happens if I miss a credit card payment?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Missing a credit card payment can have several consequences: (1) You'll be charged a late payment fee ranging from ₹100 to ₹1,300 depending on the outstanding amount. (2) Interest charges of 2.5%-3.5% per month (30%-42% annually) will be applied on the unpaid balance. (3) Your CIBIL score will be negatively impacted, making it harder to get loans or new cards in the future. (4) Repeated missed payments can lead to your card being blocked or your account being sent to collections. Always try to pay at least the minimum amount due to avoid these penalties.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top: 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Ready to Get Your Perfect Credit Card?</h3>
          <p>Compare 50+ cards, check eligibility instantly, and apply online in minutes. Our experts are here to help you choose the best card.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline">Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
